<div><b>WORKING HOURS:</b></div><div><b><br></b></div><div><span class="\&quot;Apple-tab-span\&quot;" style="\&quot;white-space:pre\&quot;">	</span>Week days (Monday to Friday): 9.00 am to 5.00 pm.&nbsp;</div><div><span class="\&quot;Apple-tab-span\&quot;" style="\&quot;white-space:pre\&quot;">	</span>The library will remain closed during Saturdays, Sundays and Government holidays.</div><div><br></div>
<div><b>CIRCULATION SERVICES:</b></div><div><b><br></b></div><div><span class="\&quot;Apple-tab-span\&quot;" style="\&quot;white-space:pre\&quot;">	</span>All the students / staff members are given an identity card bearing their bar-coded roll number / identity number. Every faculty and student is eligible to borrow five and two books at a time respectively. &nbsp;Books will be issued only on the presentation of identity cards. &nbsp;Books on dues should be returned on or before the due date. &nbsp;</div><div><br></div><div>If a book is not returned on the due date by the students, an overdue of Re.0.25 per book per day will be levied. A book may be renewed for a further period of 15 days, provided no other student/staff has reserved for the book in the meantime. &nbsp;A book will not be renewed for more than two times.</div><div><br></div><div>Faculty members are allowed to use the CIT library also. After obtaining special permission, the students can also make use of the CIT library.</div><div><br></div>
<div><b>BOOK BANK:</b></div><div><span class="\&quot;Apple-tab-span\&quot;" style="\&quot;white-space:pre\&quot;">	</span>With a view to help the poor and deserving students, a Book Bank has been functioning in the Institute since 1976. It has a collection of 700 text books. Student can get a book at the beginning of the academic year. on submission of application in the prescribed form The loan period is maximum one year.</div><div><br></div><div>&nbsp; &nbsp; <span class="\&quot;Apple-tab-span\&quot;" style="\&quot;white-space:pre\&quot;"></span>An exclusive Book Bank with a collection of 703 books was established in 1980 with a view to help the SC/ST students. Two or three books depending on the availability will be lent to each student. The maximum loan period is one academic year.</div><div><br></div><div><b>OPAC</b></div><div><b><br></b></div>
<div>OPAC (Online Public Access Catalogue) facilitates online search related to books, book bank books, journals, CD/DVDs, back volumes and standards available in the library. Users can also reserve the books which are under issue.Users can log-in the OPAC by using their Bar-coded ID/Roll number in the Member ID and Password columns. Users can change the password, if desired. OPAC can be accessed in all the intranet connected systems within the campus. Link : <strong>http://192.168.13.100:8080/AutoLib </strong> &nbsp;&nbsp;</div><div><br></div>
<div><b>E-JOURNALS</b></div><div><br></div><div>Staff and students can access the e-journals subscribed by the CIT library after getting prior permission from the Librarian of CIT. These e-journals can be accessed anywhere within our campus.</div><div><br></div>
<div><b>RULES AND REGULATIONS</b></div><div><b><br></b></div><div>*<span class="\&quot;Apple-tab-span\&quot;" style="\&quot;white-space:pre\&quot;">	</span>Complete silence is to be observed in the library.</div><div>*<span class="\&quot;Apple-tab-span\&quot;" style="\&quot;white-space:pre\&quot;">	</span>Usage of cell phone is totally prohibited inside the library.</div><div>*<span class="\&quot;Apple-tab-span\&quot;" style="\&quot;white-space:pre\&quot;">	</span>Users must keep their belongings at the \"Property Counter\" before entering the library. However they are advised not to leave valuables like mobile, calculator, purse etc.</div><div>*<span class="\&quot;Apple-tab-span\&quot;" style="\&quot;white-space:pre\&quot;">	</span>Users must register their record their Roll No/ID No in the gate register kept at the entrance while entry / exit to record to record their visit to the library.</div><div>*<span class="\&quot;Apple-tab-span\&quot;" style="\&quot;white-space:pre\&quot;">	</span>Users have to produce their bar-coded membership card to the library staff on demand.</div><div>*<span class="\&quot;Apple-tab-span\&quot;" style="\&quot;white-space:pre\&quot;">	</span>Users should leave the books and journals on the table after reading.</div><div>*<span class="\&quot;Apple-tab-span\&quot;" style="\&quot;white-space:pre\&quot;">	</span>Misplacement of books in the different shelves is punishable.</div><div>*<span class="\&quot;Apple-tab-span\&quot;" style="\&quot;white-space:pre\&quot;">	</span>Underlining, scribbling and / or tearing of pages or any other type of mutilation of books and journals, mishandling or misuse of computers will be punishable.</div><div>*<span class="\&quot;Apple-tab-span\&quot;" style="\&quot;white-space:pre\&quot;">	</span>If any book / journal is brought out of the library without proper entry, serious action will be taken.</div><div>*<span class="\&quot;Apple-tab-span\&quot;" style="\&quot;white-space:pre\&quot;">	</span>The competent authority will take necessary action against the users who violate the library systems and services.</div><div><br></div>
